# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  LS Event Manager — example environment variables
#  Copy to `.env` for local dev, and set the same values in
#  Vercel → Project Settings → Environment Variables for production.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Supabase (required) ──
# Already wired in supabase.js — these are public, scoped to the anon role.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx


# ── Cloudflare Turnstile (optional, for the public booking page) ──
#
# Activates the real CAPTCHA layer on /book/EVENT_ID. When NOT set, the page
# falls back to honeypot + cooldown + min-fill-time only (sufficient for
# casual bot prevention; insufficient against a motivated attacker).
#
# Setup steps:
#   1. Cloudflare dashboard → Turnstile → Add Site
#        Site name:  Latin Securities EventManager
#        Domain(s):  eventosv11.vercel.app  (+ localhost for dev if you want)
#        Widget mode: Managed (recommended) — or Invisible if you prefer
#                    no visible checkbox
#   2. Copy the two values Cloudflare gives you:
#        Site Key    → goes in VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY    (public, bundled into JS)
#        Secret Key  → goes in TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY        (server only)
#   3. Add both to Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables
#        (apply to Production and Preview at minimum)
#   4. Redeploy
#
# To verify after setup: open /book/EVENT_ID in an incognito window — the
# Cloudflare widget should render right above the "Confirmar reserva" button.

VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=
